100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On December 15, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva to address ongoing tensions in Eastern Europe, particularly regarding territorial disputes following the Great War. In the United States, Prohibition enforcement continued to spark significant debate, with calls for reform growing louder as illegal speakeasies flourished. Additionally, the British government faced mounting pressure over its handling of the Irish Free State's autonomy, reflecting the complexities of post-war governance.
